cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.HC. 

This paper involves game theory (strategic behavior of workers), machine learning (learning worker parameters), and optimization (job allocation). Therefore, it is likely to belong to the categories of cs.GT (game theory), cs.AI (artificial intelligence), cs.LG (machine learning), cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), and cs.HC (human-computer interaction). Among these, cs.GT is the most likely category as the paper deals with strategic behavior of workers and proposes a dominant strategy incentive compatible mechanism.
